<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Chelsea manager Frank Lampard is reportedly looking to make two new signings once the club secure a deal for Kai Havertz.</p>

<p>The Blues have been heavily active in the transfer market during this window, but Lampard is still looking to bring in a goalkeeper and a defensive midfielder, as reported by The Telegraph.</p>

<p>Bayer Leverkusen star Havertz has left the Germany national team's training camp so that he can travel to London and undergo a medical ahead of joining Chelsea.</p>

<p>Frank Lampard is eager for Chelsea to make two more signings once they bring in Kai Havertz</p>

<p>Chelsea want Rennes goalkeeper Edouard Mendy, who the French club value at £30million</p>

<p>West Ham midfielder Declan Rice is another target for Chelsea as they look to strengthen </p>

<p>Lampard wants further arrivals at Stamford Bridge and is targeting Rennes goalkeeper Edouard Mendy, who is valued at £30million by the French side.</p>

<p>In addition, Chelsea want to bring in a defensive midfielder, with West Ham's Declan Rice their primary target in that regard. </p>

<p>Chelsea are closing in on the signing of Bayer Leverkusen star Kai Havertz for £90million</p>

<p>Chelsea's total spending for this transfer window is set to exceed £200million once they sign Havertz.</p>

<p>Hakim Ziyech and Timo Werner both arrived at the club, while more recently deals have been secured for Ben Chilwell, Thiago Silva and Malang Sarr.  </p>
